<p>Despite several recommendations, I was never able to procure for myself a proper huarache while in Mexico in January. But I just had a piping hot one from Los Campos Meat Market in Boise (on Orchard). An oblong corn tortilla shaped roughly like the sole of a sandal, chorizo and white cheese. Very satisfying.</p>
